{"about_the_game":"Play this strange little idea that combines turn-based planning with old-school 2D side-scrolling.  I would call this game an experimental strategy game.  Build a deck and get a hand of cards.  Arrange those cards in the order that you want your little robot to follow.  Press play and watch your little obedient robot advance through the stage.<br><br><strong>You take control of a little obedient robot that you kind of program with cards you find.</strong><br><br>Learn your robot's movement cards by practicing with them.  Give them a try and see what each card does.  Once you know how to use them you can plan and try to dodge enemies as you make your way to the exit.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\"><strong>HOW TO PLAY:</strong></h2><br><strong>You click and drag cards into whatever order you want. </strong><br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1522540/extras/GIF_1.gif?t=1647274951\" /><br><br><strong>Then when you're ready, hit the play button and watch your robot follow the commands on the cards.</strong><br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1522540/extras/GIF_2.gif?t=1647274951\" /><br><br><strong>You can add cards to modify your robot's moves.</strong><br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1522540/extras/GIF_3.gif?t=1647274951\" /><br><br>There are numerous different stages to explore along with dozens of special moves to discover.  The game features at least 2+ hours of gameplay.<br><br><strong><i>*Please note that the game may have some bugs as it is a prototype.  We'll try to squash anything nasty we come across.</i></strong>","achievements":{"highlighted":[{"name":"Beat Level 1","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/1522540/883afdd3e13f51a736da7121f595529a785538e4.jpg"},{"name":"Beat Level 2","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steam